    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nThe Release Manager at Snowflake orchestrates timely, high-quality SaaS product delivery by coordinating engineering teams and stakeholders. This role guides releases, enhances process, and accelerates builds and deployments. Combining program management with technical expertise, the Release Manager balances risks against business objectives, operates autonomously, and defines release criteria, improves metrics, communicates status, and implements process enhancements.\n\n\nAS A RELEASE MANAGER YOU WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR:\n\n - Manage execution of the deployment plan during production deployment, including fielding of deployment issues, escalations, and contingencies, acting as the primary point of contact throughout the deployment execution.\n\n - Coordinates engineering teams and stakeholders for high-quality, fast-paced releases.\n\n - Onboards internal customers to the Release Engineering platform.\n\n - Assists with requirements and processes for the automated release platform.\n\n - Communicates release status, action items, and updates.\n\n - Assists the Support team with public communications.\n\n - Manages all release communications, schedules, landing pages, and calendar entries.\n\n - Monitors release phase progress with metrics.\n\n - Facilitates meetings to influence engineering teams to adhere to the process and minimize release related risks.\n\n - Continuously improves release processes by incorporating best practices.\n\n\nOUR IDEAL CANDIDATE WILL HAVE :\n\n - 5+ years Program/Project Management experience with Software Engineering teams.\n\n - Proven experience partnering with product and support teams.\n\n - Outstanding organizational, communication, and interpersonal skills.\n\n - Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.\n\n - Strong aptitude for quick learning in dynamic environments.\n\n - Collaborative team player with enthusiasm for new technologies and innovative solutions..\n\n - Bachelor's Degree related technical discipline.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\n - SaaS Release Manager experience.\n\n - AI tools experience.\n\n - Experience in an on-demand environment, with Agile development and 24x7 operations.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
